Source of the problem is a rare genetic abnormality. At the same time, low-sleep people do not have health problems, unlike people who consciously adjust their sleep time downwards, reducing the sleep time to 6 or less hours. Therefore, many psychologists call for people to return to normal eight hour sleep patterns, considering that the fashion for neglecting sleep for the sake of work or entertainment to be very dangerous. Among the "sleepless" are such notable figures as Leonardo da Vinci, Salvador Dali, Nikola Tesla, Margaret¬†Thatcher and Madonna.
